UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Edgar C. BRADFORD, Appellee. No. 7409. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 21, 1934. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and M. G. Gallaher, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los An-geles, Cal. Alvin Gerlaek, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
